vocabulary.definition: having or showing a strong desire and determination to succeed
vocabulary.example: She has ambitious plans to start her own business next year.

vocabulary.definition: the point at which a plan or project is realized
vocabulary.example: After years of hard work, her dream of becoming a published author finally came to fruition.

vocabulary.definition: to make full use of and derive benefit from (a resource)
vocabulary.example: The team exploited the new technology to gain a competitive advantage in the market.

vocabulary.definition: in an uncontrolled or wild manner
vocabulary.example: The virus spread rampantly throughout the city due to lack of preventive measures.

vocabulary.definition: for an unlimited or unspecified period of time
vocabulary.example: The project has been put on hold indefinitely until further funding is secured.

vocabulary.definition: a large community of plants and animals that occupies a distinct region
vocabulary.example: The rainforest biome is known for its high biodiversity and lush vegetation.
